'''''Two Jedi Men From Baronis''''' was the followup [[Jediboh Opera]] play to [[Master Thespian]] [[Damien Tantrellius]]' first play which brought him fame on [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]], ''[[Jedi Men From Baronis]]''. Though this had the same general story, it differed in that it starred Tantrellius' daughter, [[Plum Tantrellius]], who appeared in the role of [[Leia (character)|Leia]]. It also featured other members of Tantrellius' troupe, including [[Yoh Podd]] as [[Mouchus]], and the great dame [[Annah Dublavviane]] as [[Breha Organa/Legends|Leia's mother]]. It was claimed to be unmissable, although it contained some violence.

==Behind the scenes==
This play's title evokes the real-world William Shakespeare play [[Wikipedia:The Two Gentlemen of Verona|''The Two Gentlemen of Verona'']].

